ing in a second language, examining its potential and pitfalls, and bringing Carnevali's works in touch with the sociocultural context of the great wave of Italian emigration.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aAmerican literaturexItalian influences. 0aItalian American authorsy20th century. 4aAmerican Studies : Italian American Studies. 4aArea Studies : Italian Studies. 4aLiterature : Literary Criticism. 4aLiterature : Literature. 4aSociology : Ethnicity. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143847526440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438475264423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438475264/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles